 came to mean a store for provisions in general.","habitational name from Buttery (Shropshire).","English:"]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William de Butery was born about 1132. She had at least 1 daughter with William de Butery."},"et":{"Abt 1132–":"umbes 1132–Surnud","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1132–Female":"1132–Surnud","Abt 1150":"umbes 1150","Abt 1132":"umbes 1132","1132":"1132","1130":"1130","1150":"1150"},"fi":{"Abt 1132–":"noin 1132–Kuollut","1130–Male":"1130–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1132–Female":"1132–Kuollut","Abt 1150":"noin 1150","Abt 1132":"noin 1132","1132":"1132","1130":"1130","1150":"1150"},"fr":{"Abt 1132–":"environ 1132–Décédée","1130–Male":"1130–Décédé","1150–Female":"1150–Décédée","1132–Female":"1132–Décédée","Abt 1150":"environ 1150","Abt 1132":"environ 1132","1132":"1132","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","lifeSummary":"Mrs William de Butery est née environ 1132. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec William de Butery."},"de":{"Abt 1132–":"um 1132–Verstorben","1130–Male":"1130–Verstorben","1150–Female":"1150–Verstorben","1132–Female":"1132–Verstorben","Abt 1150":"um 1150","Abt 1132":"um 1132","1132":"1132","1130":"1130","1150":"1150","lifeSummary":"Mrs William de But